If we assume the `productPrice` is populated by an api call.
Inside the `render` function we can put a check to detect when the api call gets finished, your code will look something like this -:

    componentDidMount(){
        this.setState({loading: true});
        apiCallFunction().then((response) =&gt; {
            // Your processing for the `productPrice` property
            this.setState({loading: false});
        });
    }

    render(){
        if(this.state.loading){
            return (&lt;Spinner // css spinner/&gt;)
        } else {
            return // your component that you currently have. 
        }
    }

This will avoid the `changing an uncontrolled input of type integer to be controlled` error.

